social_posts.post_text: Finished my first @americanflattrack Super Twins race in 12th. Had a great start and was running as high as 8th! I’d like to thank @competitionwerkes @mvagustausa for the amazing opportunity to race the #F3RR this year, as I’ve decided to call it a season and miss the final @motoamerica round due to some unforeseen obstacles. I knew going into this year I had a major challenge jumping into the Supersport class with being the only MV racing, having basically no spare parts (just don’t crash😆), figuring out the Next-Gen Supersport Electronics, and facing the high level of competition the class has. Unfortunately I grossly underestimated this challenge and with my other racing programs going on, I wasn’t able to give the MV program the attention it needed to be as successful as it could’ve. We had a great debut at the Ridge with a 6th place finish as I fought for a top 5 the whole race. Laguna’s result of 10th place in the extended 37 lap race was good considering I had no quick-change wheel setup or quick-fuel system to have a competitive pit stop. And COTA was challenging in the heat and my races were back-to-back with Super Hooligans. I got less than 5 minutes between races Saturday to try to recover in the 107 degree heat, and my body couldn’t. I got a bad start and finished 11th when the race got red-flagged. The result didn’t reflect how hard and well I rode, as I was making 1-2 passes per lap fighting against faster bikes that just kept passing me on the straights while simultaneously having electronics issues I had to ride around☹️ Sunday I didn’t even get an opportunity to go out for race 2 because of an even tighter schedule and the fact I was on the podium accepting my Super Hooligan trophies at the time they sent Supersport race 2 out on track. So a real unlucky scheduling situation in Austin. As far as the bike goes, it has been so much fun to ride 😃 I’d like to apologize to Competition Werkes and MV Agusta, as well as all of my sponsors for the shortcomings of the effort. It’s too early to say what the plan is for 2024, but my feeling is that I’d like to get some legitimate testing in during this off-season so I can be well prepared to come back racing 🙂 Thanks for the support everyone! #motoamerica #mvagusta 📸 @brianjnelsonphoto
